# Supabase Configuration
# Get these from: https://supabase.com/dashboard/project/YOUR_PROJECT/settings/api

# Your Supabase project URL (looks like: https://xxxxxxxxxxxxx.supabase.co)
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=your_supabase_url_here

# Your Supabase anon/public key (starts with: eyJ...)
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your_supabase_anon_key_here

# OpenAI API Key (optional - for AI features)
# Get from: https://platform.openai.com/api-keys
VITE_OPENAI_API_KEY=your_openai_api_key_here

# ========================================
# INSTRUCTIONS FOR LOCAL DEVELOPMENT:
# ========================================
# 1. Copy this file to .env in your project root
# 2. Replace the placeholder values with your actual credentials
# 3. Never commit .env file to git (it's in .gitignore)
# 4. Restart your dev server after changing .env

# ========================================
# INSTRUCTIONS FOR VERCEL DEPLOYMENT:
# ========================================
# 1. Go to: https://vercel.com/dashboard
# 2. Select your project
# 3. Go to: Settings → Environment Variables
# 4. Add each variable:
#    - VITE_SUPABASE_URL
#    - VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY
#    - VITE_OPENAI_API_KEY (optional)
# 5. Set for: Production, Preview, Development (all 3)
# 6. Redeploy your site

# ========================================
# HOW TO GET SUPABASE CREDENTIALS:
# ========================================
# 1. Go to: https://supabase.com/dashboard
# 2. Select your project (or create one)
# 3. Click: Settings (gear icon) → API
# 4. Copy:
#    - Project URL → VITE_SUPABASE_URL
#    - anon public key → VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY

# ========================================
# TROUBLESHOOTING:
# ========================================
# If login doesn't work:
# - Check that variables are set correctly (no quotes, no spaces)
# - Ensure Supabase URL starts with https://
# - Ensure Supabase key starts with eyJ
# - Restart dev server after changing .env
# - Check browser console for error messages
